<div id="PJA11d067" class="doc letter">

<h2>From C. W. F. Dumas</h2>

<div class="docbody" xml:lang="fra">
<div class="opener">
<table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		  <td class="salutationLeft">Monsieur</td>
		  <td class="salutationRight">Lahaie 29e. Janv. 1781</td>
		</tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>Dans ma Lettre dhier il y a une erreur qui doit tre redresse. Ce nest point parce quon attend un Courier de Petersbourg, que le Manifeste na pas encore t publi, mais parce que les villes dAmsterdam et de Dort ne sont point contentes de celui qui est dress, ne le trouvent pas assez fort, et veulent quon en fasse un autre. Voil la seule raison qui a retard celui-ci; et lon en fera un autre.</p>
<p>Votre prdiction, Monsieur, dune convulsion dont lAngleterre est menace,<a class="ptr" href="#PJA11d068n1" id="PJA11d068n1-ptr">1</a> pourroit bien saccomplir plutt que vous ne pensez. Les grains sont fort chers en Angleterre. Ce qui cotoit cent, est aujourdhui  175. La Livre de pain cote  Londres 10 pence: on y craint une Rvolte.</p>
<p>Probablement la rep. fera dans peu la dmarche de demander  la France le secours de ses forces aux Indes orientales. On la propos au Str, qui la approuv.</p>
<p>Le Courier expdi dici  Petersb. pour demander les secours de la Convention, nest parti qui le 12 de ce mois, ainsi il ne pourra guere tre de retour que vers le 20e. du prochain.</p>
<span class="pb center" title="page number in print edition" id="ADMS-06-11-02-pb-0087">[87<a style="padding-left: 0px" onclick="window.open('/img-document-get.xqy?image=ADMS/Pages/ADMS-06-11/ADMS-06-11-02-pb-0087.jpg', 'pageImage', 'scrollbars=1,resizable=1'); return false" onkeypress="this.onclick();" tabindex="0" title="Click to view image of page from print edition"><img src="/img-ML/page-icon.gif" width="18" height="20" style="vertical-align:middle;" alt="page icon"/></a>]</span>
<p>On garnit nos ctes contre des descentes qui paroissent peu  craindre  cause des bancs qui les bordent. Vous tes, Monsieur,  mme plus que moi de voir si la mme diligence est employe pour lquipement de la Flotte. Je suis avec le plus vrai respect &amp; attachement Monsieur Votre trs-obissant serviteur</p>
<div class="closer">
<p class="signed">Dumas</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div id="PJA11d068" class="trans letter">

<h2>C. W. F. Dumas to John Adams: A Translation</h2>
 
<div class="docbody">
<div class="opener">
<table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		  <td class="salutationLeft">Sir</td>
		  <td class="salutationRight">The Hague, 29 January 1781</td>
		</tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>In yesterdays letter I made an error which must be corrected. It is not the awaited arrival of the St. Petersburg courier that has delayed the publication of the manifesto, but rather that the cities of Amsterdam and Dordrecht are not satisfied with the current one. They find it too weak and want it redone. This is the only reason for its delay, and another one will be drafted.</p>
<p>Your prediction, sir, that England may be threatened by an uprising,<a class="ptr" href="#PJA11d068n1" id="PJA11d068n1-ptr">1</a> may happen sooner than you think. Grain is very expensive in England. It used to cost one hundred and today costs one hundred and seventy-five. A pound of bread costs ten pence in London. A revolt is feared.</p>
<p>It is likely the republic will soon make a dmarche requesting French assistance for its forces in the East Indies. It was proposed to the Stadholder, who approved it.</p>
<p>The courier sent to St. Petersburg to request assistance under the convention did not leave until the 12th of this month and therefore he could not possibly return sooner than the 20th of February.</p>
<p>Our coasts are garrisoned against attack which we hardly fear because of the shoals that line them. You, sir, are even more able than I am to see if the same diligence is applied to outfitting the fleet. I am with the most genuine respect and attachment, sir, your very obedient servant</p>
<div class="closer">
<p class="signed">Dumas</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="docback">
<div class="note-source" id="PJA11d068sn1">

   <p>
